Harry D. McCLEARY, Appellant, v. UNITED STATES of America, Appellee. No. 7102. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. May. 16, 1933. Smith, Mahan & Smith, of Helena, Mont., and Howard Toole and W. E. Moore, both of Missoula, Mont., for appellant. Wellington D. Rankin, U. S. Atty., Sam D. Goza, Jr., and D. L. Egnew, Asst. U. S. Attys., and D. D. Evans, Chief Atty., U. S. Veterans’ Administration, all of Helena, Mont., for appellee.

Before WILBUR, SAWTELLE, and MACK, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon consideration of the record and briefs filed in above cause, and after oral argument of counsel for the respective parties, ordered judgment of the District Court in this cause affirmed upon the decision of this court in Falbo v. United States, No. 6965, 64 F.(2d) 948.
